column_.text_:
These are notes Lilith took while conducting research in
Phondam. I'll leave them with you for safekeeping.
Found him! Whatcha doing here, Id?
Looking for a way to save Rolan.
This place is replete with his memory.
We really appreciate it, Id. You chipping in to rescue Rolan.
I owe him just as much as you do... More, even.

I feel bad intruding on his home without permission, but there might
be clues around. Wanna help us search?
Hello there. Did I hear you mention Rolan?
Huh? Oh, yeah. You a friend of his too?

So my ears didn't deceive me! We've met before, remember? At the
docks of Tempeal...
Oh! You're the guy that told us about hallowed ground!

The very same! But, um... Back to Rolan. Would you happen to
know where he is? I can't seem to get in touch.
Oh. He's... He's, um...
He's somewhere far away.
He might not come back, actually...
He's somewhere far away.
He's somewhere far away.
Yeah. Really far... It'll probably take him a while to get back...
He might not come back, actually...
He might not come back, actually...

What? When did you become a glass-half-empty kinda person?
There's gotta be a chance! It might take half a miracle, but...

That's fine. I just wanted to be sure he was safe. Knowing Rolan,
he'll probably wander in through that door when we need him most.
Though, to be honest, I hope that's sooner rather than later...
Why's that? Is something wrong?

Well... As you may know, in addition to being a vicar, Rolan was the
local Mr. Fix It. And I'm not just talking repairs...

Monster-hunting, herb-pickingâ€”he was a real lifesaver. But now
that Rolan's gone, there's tons of work that's going unfinished.
I'll do it.
Huh?
I'll take up his mantle.

This is so painful to watch. Will somebody please teach this kid to
speak like a normal person?

I think Id meant to say he just wants to be helpful, now that Rolan's
gone. Right, Id?
Right...
Oh! Well, that's very kind of you. But, um, how do I put this?

We were comfortable asking Rolan for favors because we trusted
him. While you certainly look like an upstanding young man, you're
still a stranger. No offense...
But I...
We'll help out too.
We'll help out too.
We'll help out too.

Great idea! Hey, mister, we aren't strangers. What if we tagged
along?

Well, all right. If you insist. I have to say, though, you've done so
much for our city, I feel guilty piling more work on you...
You sure about this, ?
You sure about this, ?
Yeah. It's what Rolan would want.
No problem. The more the merrier.
Yeah. It's what Rolan would want.
Yeah. It's what Rolan would want.
Um... Thanks.
No problem. The more the merrier.
No problem. The more the merrier.

For sure! There's no way we'd let you pick up the slack all by
yourself!
Yeah, yeah...

Well, now that everything's settled, I'll forward all our jobs to the
Crew Alliance Rafale.

Whenever you feel like taking something on, head over to the Quest
Counter. Thank you again, and best of luck!

Today's Id's big fixer-upper debut! Let's all do our best to
help him!

Find the goblins, recover the supplies. Sounds simple
enough.
It will be. Combat's your forte, isn't it?
It'll be easy. The goblins will probably run as soon as they see you.
Aaand there's our gobbers.
I'll make this quick!
Look out! Here comes the backup brigade!
We'll manage. Keep picking them off!
Dang, Id! I'm glad you're on our side now! This is a cakewalk!
You hear that, Id?
Um. Glad to be of help.
Whew, that's that. Let's grab the stuff and get outta here.
This should be it. Let's move on!
Hey, wait! Did you forget what we're here for?
Something's watching us... Stay sharp.
More goblins... But they shouldn't be much of a threat.

I dunno. Kinda weird they're attacking with such a small
band.
Agreed. Though I don't sense reinforcements.
Ah! A wyvern!

It's called Skywyrm Valley for a reason! Brace yourselves,
everyone!
Sure explains why there weren't many goblins...

No. Local goblins should know how to defend themselves
against wyverns. There must be more at play here.

That takes care of the flyin' lizard, but... No sight of the
stuff we came for.
We'll just have to keep looking. Let's go!

Hmm... Do you guys ever wonder how Rolan was handling all
these quests by himself?

He certainly has a knack for them, doesn't he? You really can
"leave it to Mr. Fix It."
Hey! Did you guys see that? Something big just flew by.
Not part of the brief, not part of our problem...
Another goblin. Let's take it out before it notices us.
More of them! Here they come.
Something's wrong! They're all running, but not from us!
Doesn't matter. We came here to do one thing: destroy them.
Another goblin band! What gives?!
I don't know, but it looks like our hunch was right!
That was the last of them. Now, let's retrieve those supplies.

That's two of three accounted for, so now we should have
just one more.
Didn't know you were such a poet. That wasn't half-bad!
Whoa... Katalina! You sounded just like Siero! Hehe...
Wait, no, Iâ€”my sense of humor is far less pun reliant!
I don't get it. Was something humorous just now?
Oh, it's nothing, Id. Don't break your brain over a little joke.
What joke?

All right, enough messing around. There's the last supply
pack.
We have to take out these goblins first!
What was that? Stay alert!
No way... Nobody said anything about a griffin!

Well, this explains why the goblins were fleeingâ€”no one
wants to be griffin lunch!

It wasn't in the request, but we can't have it stirring up any
more monsters.
In which case... we better take it down!
Heeey, now you're startin' to sound like a real Mr. Fix It.
We've got the edge! Keep it up and the day will be ours!

There's no telling what it will do with its back cornered.
Be careful!

We've worn it down! A few more shots, and bird brains is
done for!
Nice! It's on its last legs. Get 'em, Id!
On it.
Not good! Proceed with caution!
It's going to charge! Get out of its path!
We did it! Haha... that sure was an adventure!

Missionâ€”I mean, quest complete. Now to bring the items
back to the client.
Yeesh, you're all business, huh?
Go easy on him. He's still new to all this.
Hey, I heard about the job! Thanks a million!
You should be thanking Id.
You know, I think Id would make a great Mr. Fix It...
You should be thanking Id.
You should be thanking Id.
Yep! We couldn't have done it without him!

You know, I think Id would make a great Mr. Fix It until Rolan comes
back.

You know, I think Id would make a great Mr. Fix It until Rolan comes
back.

Heh, I'd be a fool if I turned down someone who's garnered your
seal of approval!

Id, the citizens of Tempeal would be honored if you kept serving our
city. And... I'm sorry that I ever doubted you.
Why be sorry?
Uh...

Um, I think Id meant to say that you don't need to apologize. That
he's happy to help. Right, Id?
Ah. Yeah.
Lyria, when did you learn to speak Id?
Hehe... I mean, doesn't he remind you of a certain someone?
Haha! Right? I've heard rocks who talk more than these two!
Wait, really?
I speak plenty! I think...
Wait, really?
Wait, really?

Uh, yeah? You mostly just go "mhm" and "nuh-uh" and stuff, until
you need to make a decision.
I speak plenty! I think...
I speak plenty! I think...
Don't worry about it. You know what they say: silence is golden.

Exactly. You might not talk the talk, but you certainly walk the walk.
I know this city will be safe in your hands.
They never would've trusted me without your help. So thank you.
No worries. Let's make Rolan proud.
No worries. Let's make Rolan proud.
No worries. Let's make Rolan proud.

We owe that guy our lives. Least we could do is help him with the
housekeeping.

Yep. Not to mention we even found his journal. Talk about a
coinkydink.

It truly is a priceless keepsake. His memories are etched across
these pages.

He musta been super busy putting out fires to drop this and not
even notice.

Hehe, I dunno. Our boy Rolan sounds exactly like the type to have
his head in the clouds.

You know, if we keep running errands, maybe we'll find more of his
belongings!

Good point. By retracing his footsteps, we could discover a way to
rescue him.

Speaking of his footsteps... Id, if I may, there's one point I would like
to emphasize.
What?

Skill wasn't the only reason Rolan was so beloved. There was also
the way he carried himselfâ€”how gentle he was.

That's for sure. I'd ask Rolan for directions in a heartbeat. On the
other hand, you always look like you just sniffed a garbage can.
So what should I do?
Hmm... You could try smiling more?
Okay...
Heh.
That's how someone would smile... if they were sitting on hot coal.

Oh! I know! Id, why don't you try acting like Rolan? We can start
with how he talks.
Just leave it to Mr. Fix Id!
Now, your turn!
Just leave it to Mr. Fix It.
Uh. Wow.
Uh. Wow.
We've got a long way to go...
That wasn't so bad. What's next?

Rolan never got the chance to finish this mission. Well, it's the
least we can do for him.

I know this is Rolan's journal, but I'm sure he would be all right
with us reading it.

Here's another mission Rolan got pulled away from. Maybe
he left behind a clue we can use.
It looks like you've got the hang of handyman work now, Id.
You think so?

I know so! Everyone in town says they can come to you with
their problems!
Just focus on what you can do and give it 110%.
Someone's fired up. Don't worry, we've got your back!

Don't take this the wrong way, Id, but how 'bout relaxing a
bit? You look out of it lately.

The dragon power inside me feels like it's... pulsating? I don't
know how to describe it.

Well, hopefully it's nothing, but let us know right away if it
gets worse!

The receptionist at the Quest Counter said there's a huge
stack of thank-you lettersâ€”all for Id!
Guess that proves Id's got this fix-it stuff down pat!

Still feels like I'm learning the ropes, but I'm glad I've
been useful.

That's... a dragon! What kind of craziness did you get into, 
Rolan?
Ooh, now we can take even tougher requests!
Bring it on. I'll do whatever needs to be done.
Id!
Hey, Mr. Id. Are you done with work?
Yep, more or less.

Woo-hoo! I'm ready for my next sword lesson! Meet me at the
church, okay?
Guess a few swings couldn't hurt.
Yes!
Well, well, well. Look at Mr. Popular over here.

Playing with the children was apparently part of Rolan's job too.
Unfortunately, all I can do is teach them how to swing swords.
They're lucky to have a great teacher!
Wow, poor you.
They're lucky to have a great teacher!
They're lucky to have a great teacher!
If you say so.
Wow, poor you.
Wow, poor you.
Fine... It's not that bad.

Heehee. Meanwhile, we've been finding more of Rolan's journals.
Let's keep our eyes peeled!
Of course.

All right, Rolan. What else did you leave behind? Guess we'll 
find out soon enough.
Wow, Id! You really can do anything!

All of these tough missions have really put me through my paces. 
But maybe I'm better for it.
By the way, how's that dragon power been treatin' ya lately?

I've had this sense of foreboding for a while now. Like
someone's watching me.
Huh. As if Versa is watching me...

This journal was written by an "Astraeus." We're on the right
track.
Done with the job already? You guys never fail to impress.
Any other requests?

Technically, yes, but... I know it's not really my place to say this, but
maybe you should take the rest of the day off.

You've already done wonders for our city, and we're grateful for the
help. The last thing we want is our heroes overworking themselves.
I'll drink to that! How about it, Id? First round's on me.
Sorry, but I think I'll pass.

Heh. Well, at least you let me down gently. The old you wouldn't
have bothered with an apology at all.

I'll say. You started off at, like, thorny cactusâ€”but now, you're 
more like brick wall.
Thanks, I guess. Being around the crew helps.

Look at that, you even learned humility! Now work on that smile,
and you'll be two steps from Prince Charming in no time.
Uh-huh...

On the other hand, folks like the tall, dark, and silent type. Just keep
up the good work, and I'm sure this city will accept you as the new
Mr. Fix Id in no time flat.
Oh! Thank goodness you're here!
What's happened?

Something urgent. I'll explain, butâ€”let me introduce you to the
captain of Seedhollow's forces.

He heard rumors of your good work and traveled all this way to
meet you. Says he's got an important mission.

First off, I'd like to thank all of you for saving Seedhollow. And, Id, I
don't know if you remember, but we've actually met before.

Or maybe I should say "fought" before. When you were still working
for the ringleader of Avia.
I remember.
We promise Id's changed now!

Don't worry. I've already heard about how he joined your crew and
took down Lilith.

I've also been informed that he's now helping rebuild our war-torn
city. Or am I mistaken?
No. I'm committed.

I wish we had the luxury of time to explore your motives, but
unfortunately, there's something I need to request of you...
Ask away.
Ask away.

I'm sure you're already acquainted with the new tower looming
above Seedhollow Castle?
Thing is, the Church is gone, but it's still there.

We kept a close eye on it, and it seems to have lost all its power. It's
just floating along, like a big rock in the sky.

Hm... That makes sense. There was a primal beast acting as its
core, but it's no longer here.

Well, a few days ago, I figured it was safe enough to send soldiers in
to investigate.

We discovered a bunch of monsters shaped like shadow people. We cleaned
most of them up ourselves, but there was one that was... different.
Different how?

I'd never felt anything like it. We were overwhelmed by waves of
dark energyâ€”our forces couldn't even get close.

Luckily, it didn't seem keen on leaving the tower, but with a threat
that big, it's better not to take chances. That's why I'm here.
Ready for some ghost-busting?
Sure you don't need a breather first?
Ready for some ghost-busting?
Ready for some ghost-busting?
Of course.
Avia summoned that tower, so it's my responsibility to tear it down.
Sure you don't need a breather first?
Sure you don't need a breather first?
I'm fine. Let's just move.

Hold on. You're only gonna ask him? I wouldn't mind a breather
myself, you know...

Thank you. I know this is a lot to ask, so I'm registering the mission
with the Crew Alliance. You'll be fairly compensated for your service.

Hate to make you guys rush, but could you start heading out?
Please! We need you!

Sometimes I wish we only took easy missions... No point
complainin' now though.

Wonder what these shadow-thingies are... Guess we'll find
out soon!
This place makes my scales stand up...
Yeah... I don't wanna stay here any longer than we have to.

Eugh, what are they? Are these supposed to be our shadow
monsters?

Perhaps, but they're not our primary target. The soldier
mentioned one exceptionally powerful shade.
Ready your weapons!

There's more lurking in the area. We can't let them roam
free.
They keep on appearing! Just how many are there?
Doesn't matter. We'll get them all!
Let's keep moving.
Um, Id? Are you doing all right?
...I am. This place just brings back memories.
This was where Lilith...
I can only imagine how it must feel to be back...
Sorry, I'm... I'm fine, really. Don't worry about me.
If you're sure...
Nrgh, we can never catch a break!
Luckiest skyfarers in Zegagrande!
Id, uh... I don't wanna be annoying, but you sure you're okay?

I'll be fine. Not that that'll stop you goody two shoes from
fussing over me.
Hah! Got that right! You're one of us now.
There. Let's find more.
Wait. I sense something, but I can't put a finger on what.
This air is oddly stifling...
H-hang on, that looks like Id!
It's like my shadow? What the hell is going on?

I don't understand either, but it doesn't look open to
questions! Get ready for a fight!
What is this thing? Why does it look like me?!

It might be part of the pillar's defenses. Just like the shadow
clone of Furycane we fought here before.

Well, whatever it is, I'm taking it down. This has to be our
mark!
Must be weird fighting yourself, but we've got your back!
This thing's tough! It picked the right guy to rip off.
Tease me after we've killed it!
Still can't tell when you're getting a compliment, can ya?
We're cooking now! Keep it up, people!
Roger that! Though this thing still creeps me out...
I'll end this!
It's gathering its strength!
Here it comesâ€”keep your distance!
Hang on, is it gonnaâ€”
Just keep dodging! It can't attack forever!
You'd know best! Sheesh, it's just like when we fought you!
Here it comes again!
Stay calm. We know how to handle this!
It can copy the dragon's powers too!
It's using the same tricks! We can get through this!
Enough of this!
It's down! Now's our chance!
Don't back down!
It's done. You okay, Id?
Weirdly, I think I actually needed that.

After going toe to toe with the dragon's destructive power, I
swear I can tackle anything now.

I heard about your victory! On behalf of all the citizens of
Seedhollow, thank you. You've done our city a great service.

Always happy to lend a hand. If you ever need help again, you know
who to call.

Keep watching that tower though. A creepy place like that makes a
perfect lair for monsters.

We'll be sure to set a watch. And I'll personally inform you of any
developments.

Well, it's about time I went back to Seedhollow. Thanks again, and
take care.
You aren't going to arrest me?
Id?

You're the local Mr. Fix It. The city depends on you. Why would I take
you into custody?
It's my past, I've... Well...

It is true you were one of Lilith's accomplices. And while I am
interested in hearing an insider's take on Avia's crusades, now's not
the time.

After you complete a few more requests for us, why don't you invite
me back to Folca, as one of your loyal clients? Then we can have a
chat over tea or something.
Thanks for understanding.
Thanks for understanding.
Thanks for understanding.
Least I could do for our heroes. Now, I should probably get going.

You truly are something special. Even professional soldiers couldn't
take down that monster!
Fighting's about all I'm good for.

You need to stop putting yourself down like that. Hubris is bad,
sure, but a little self-confidence never hurt anyone.

You've improved the lives of the people in our city. That's something
to be proud of.
But I...

Listen, Id. I know you're new to this positive feedback thing, but just
take the compliment, will ya?
I'm proud to be of service...
But I'm still nothing like Rolan.
You don't need to be like Rolan. Just be the best version of yourself.
Heh. That's what Lyria keeps telling me.
Yep. You're your own person, Id!
Okay, got it... Guess I'll give it a shot.
Hey, you. Come back when there's more jobs.

Hah... Okay, why don't we try staying true to ourselves while
working on our communication skills? Remember what we
practiced, Id?
Oh, right...
Just leave it to Mr. Fix Id.
Hehe, the townspeople sure love their Mr. Fix Id.

They've been keeping me busy, but I'm free enough to find
more clues.
Oh, sweet! New jobs got added.
Nice. Can't wait to see what's available.
Look alive! This dragon is brimming with elemental power!

What kinda research brought Fix It Dude out here? The mysteries 
never end with that guy!
That's not the problem right now...

Another dragon. I guess that means we can expect more after
this one... Great.
Guess we're going home empty-handed today.

C'mon. Fix It Dude's kinda forgetful, but his pockets aren't
that loose.

Not sure if there's four or six dragons in total, but we can 
worry about the math after we've slain them.

Aw, no journal this time. I can't believe I'm saying this, but I
wish Rolan was more careless...
This looks like our hardest one yet. Let's do this!
There's something else here. Some kind of weird book.

Hey, bud? I don't think there's any butt left to kick around
here.

Hey, bud? I don't think there's any butt left to kick around
here.
Hey! We gotta get back and teach those bad guys a lesson!
Wait, where are you going? Not thinkin' of running, are ya?
Did you get lost or something? The enemy's that way.

I hate to tell you this, bud... But you're going in the wrong
direction.

I hate to tell you this, bud... But you're going in the wrong
direction.
Hey, uh, pal? Did you forget where we're going?
Hey, uh, pal? Did you forget where we're going?
The Dragon Trial... This ain't gonna be easy.

I'm gettin' real bad vibes from this place... You gonna be
okay?
We're not up against the dragon... It's up against us! Let's go!

It's just a humongous, powerful dragon! What could go
wrong?
Nothin' to be afraid of... We got this!
Places, people! We've dealt with worse than dragons!
Hehe! We sure showed it who's boss, huh?
We passed the Dragon Trial!
Yeah, we did it! Hehe, that was easy!
You ready to rock?
C'mon... It's go time!
That was awesome... You were awesome!
On your marks, get set... Go mash some monsters!
We'll have the baddies cleaned out in no time!
Heh! Ready to bust some baddies?
Looks like we found their leader!
That one looks tougher than the others... Be careful!
We'll show it who's the real boss around these parts!

That should be the last of 'em... Which means, quest
complete!
It's over already? Boy, you're on a roll!
Hehe! You made that look easy!
Clock's ticking! Let's gooo!
We've got this!
Yeah! This'll be a breeze!
Uh oh... Here comes trouble.
That was one heck of a fight, but I knew I could count on you!

Those Avia jerks are causin' trouble again? Not on our
watch!
Uh-oh! This guy looks strong. You better watch out!
Hahaha! We sure showed them!
They're bringin' the whole circus, huh? Keep on your toes!
Look alive! We've got company!
Looks like they're comin' for us! You ready?
Baddie alert! It's go time!
Watch out! Here they come!
If they want a fight, they've got one!
Uh oh! Go get 'em!
They just keep comin'... But we'll show 'em who's boss!
Not likin' the look of this... B-but don't let it intimidate ya!
How many of them are there? Don't let 'em swarm you!
Straight ahead!
Behind us!
On your right!
On your left!
Haha! Take that!
Whew... I'm beat. Can we take five?

That's one wave down, but looks like there's still more of
'em!

Looks like we've got a second to catch our breath before
things heat up again.

Good work! Keep it up, and we'll finish the next wave in no
time!

Aaand, I think that's everything! You were awesome out
there!
We just gotta take out any monsters we see, right? Easy!
I think we're good here. Let's move to the next spot!
That should take care of this area. The next zone awaits!
All secure! We should check the next area quick!

And stay out! Heh, we kicked some serious butt there! Let's
keep it up!
Not a single baddie left... Let's go check out the next place!

C'mon, we gotta keep movin'! There's still baddies hiding
somewhere.

We should hurry to the next area... Who knows what could be
happenin'?

Are we gonna check out the next zone or what? I'm pretty
sure there's nothin' left here!
Huh? Where are you goin'? There's still goons to bash!
Hold up! Let's finish off the enemies here first.
We can't just leave! We gotta get rid of the enemies!
We've just gotta keep this thing safe... How hard can it be?

Nothin's breakin' our defenses! This place has never been
safer!

Hey! There's enemies on the way! We can't let them trash the
hallowed ground!
Looks like we've got guests! Go give 'em a big welcome!
Yikes! Someone stop them!
We're not doin' great, but we can still turn this around!
Things're lookin' real bad! Stop the attackers at all cost!
Yeah! We did it!
No way! How... How could we let this happen?
All righty! We've just gotta grab what the client asked for.

We're not in a rush yet, but I'm sure our client wouldn't mind
a little hustle!

Clock's tickin', buddy... The client's expecting us back soon,
so we've gotta hurry!

Hey, we're runnin' really short on time...You tryin' to milk
every second?

You're making good progress! At this rate, you'll finish the
quest no problem.

Wow! You're one heck of a sleuth! Looks like we're in great
shape!
Man, keep it up! We'll be finished in no time!

Looks like we got everything we need, but we might as well
see if we can bag some extra.

It's about time we headed back and showed the client what
you found!

Whoa, you found way more than we needed! The client's
gonna be over the moon!

Uh-oh, we're surrounded... Try to hold out until
reinforcements get here!
Not outta the woods yet... Hang in there!
Stay cool, guys. Help's on the way!
Keep it up! Backup should get here soon!
They're here! Everything worked out in the end...
Stay alert! Don't let anything get the jump on you.
Lookin' good so far. You got this!
There's still enemies left, but you can take 'em!
We're in the home stretch now! Keep it up!
That's one more quest in the bag!
Slimes... Better act quick before they run!
There's still some slimes left, right? Hop to it!
Go, go, go! Smash those pots!
Last push! Make sure you get 'em all!
Look at the size of that goo-lossus! Don't let it escape!
Hehe... Now that was a blast! You were amazing!
Crying for help, ya big weenie?
Capture them at once!

Red alert! All units report to the stern! Permission to
eliminate on sight!
Why haven't they been captured yet!
Ergh! Damn, they're tough!
Now the port guns are down! What in blazes is going on!
They're targeting the guns! Stop them now!
The regulator is under attack! Protect it with your lives!
The ship can't take any more damage!
Nope, nothing to see this way.

Explorin' with baddies on our tails is no fun! Let's give
ourselves some breathing room!
Awesome! Now we can get closer!
Now's our chance to hit back! You guys, ready?
Is it frozen in fear or somethin'? That's our cue!
Its guard is down! Go, go, go!
You know the drill! It's payback time!
C'mon, guys! Let's knock his scales off!
Ain't gonna get a better chance than this!
Nice! Keep those hits comin'!
Serve up a big helping of "ouch!"
Yeah, just like that!
We're gonna ram him! Hold onto somethin', guys!
That wasn't enough! We have to stop him, no matter what!
